span.span: The Gilmore City-Bradgate Elementary School welcomes children for 3-year-old Preschool through Sixth Grade.We are in a whole grade sharing partnership with West Bend-Mallard for grades 7 through 12.

The Gilmore City-Bradgate school district, in its educational programs, have a process to assist students experiencing behavior and learning difficulties. The building assistance teams are responsible for this process. Representatives from the Prairie Lakes Area Education Agency atwww.plaea.orgmay also assist the school districts in this process. Parents wanting access to this process should contact the schools principal.
A Great Start Close to Home
Every child is a skilled reader.
Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics are an integral part of our learning.
Our school belongs to the community. We welcome and encourage community involvement.
Our kids are thinkers, dreamers, doers, innovators and creators.
Our kids benefit from the personal attention and relationships that are part of being
Technology helps us connect our students to the world.
We find solutions and expect the best from everyone!
Bagged meals for breakfast, lunch and dinner.

It is the policy of the Gilmore City-Bradgate Community School District not to illegally discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, disability, religion, creed, age (for employment), marital status (for programs), sexual orientation, gender identity and socioeconomic status (for programs) in its educational programs and its employment practices. There is a grievance procedure for processing complaints of discrimination. If you have questions or a grievance related to this policy please contact the districts Equity Coordinator, Jose Herrera , SchoolCounselor, at 515-373-6124 (school) or e-mail atjherrera@gcb.k12.ia.us.
